text:
While there are officially more than 13,000 confirmed cases of COVID-19 in the Philippines, there are actually over 19,000 people who have tested positive for the disease.
The gap between the two has gone up by 2,151% or 22 times since April 2, acc. to @ABSCBNNews Data Analytics. https://t.co/FpSdwkmwmh
